  "text": "Helical filaments at the abscission sites. According to the current model, cytokinetic abscission is driven by the ESCRT III complex, which organizes into helical spirals located in the region between the dark zone and the abscission sites [CITATION_1] . Consistently, helical spirals were previously detected and characterized in this region by EM tomography [CITATION_2] . These structures are transient and are thought to form in late stages of abscission and to Figure S1 . n = 5. Scale bar = 2 μ m.",
